headline: This week in business: Taylor Swift, Tesla, and some cleaner Walmart snacks
summary: FICO is cutting out the middleman, Walmart is cutting artificial dyes, Starbucks is cutting stores, and Taylor Swift is cutting a new deal with theaters.

headline: Starbucks’s Roller Coaster Week of Job Cuts and Store Closures
summary: In  Starbucks’s  Seattle headquarters, it was known as “Project Bloom.”  Launched earlier this year, the hush-hush undertaking evaluated thousands of the company’s coffee shops across North America on profitability, and the experience of customers and baristas.  It was Starbucks’s second round of corporate layoffs in less than a year under Chief Executive  Brian Niccol  and among the chain’s biggest closing of cafes since 2008.
